n questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 1: you have used 60 actions; a strong score needs about 39 or fewer. You are 1.5x over the target.\nIf you are not steadily making progress toward the level goal, commit to your single best hypothesis and the shortest sequence that tests it \u2014 do not exhaustively scan rows/columns or enumerate every option. Test one idea, read the result, then decide.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "The green bar is at 4 pixels. The UP action moved the blue bar. Let me check the result to see if the game ended or if there's any new info. I need to check `last_action_result` for `game_over`, `level_completed`, or `done`.\nActually, the result shows `state: \"NOT_FINISHED\"`, `done: false`, `level_completed: false`, `game_over: false`. So the game is still running.\nThe green bar decreases by about 2-3 pixels per action. At 4 pixels, I have about 1-2 more actions.\nI'm completely stuck on this level. Let me try one more thing: what if the goal is to move the blue bar to the EXACT position of one of the yellow shapes? The yellow shapes are at rows 52-59, but the blue bar can only reach rows 44-47 at the bottom. So that's not possible.\nWait, what if I need to move the blue bar to the LEFT yellow shape's column range? The left yellow is at cols 16-27. The blue bar is 20 cols wide. So if I position it at cols 16-35, it would overlap with the left yellow shape's columns.\nFro